The leaves, fruits, seeds, and bark of the 
 M. balsamina contains secondary metabolites such as alkaloids, flavonoids, glycosides, steroids, terpenes, cardiac glycoside, saponins, tannins and lectins (
 Talukdar and Hossain, 2014). The matured seeds are the main source of plant lectins (
 Abegunde et al., 2018). The primary metabolites include crude lipid (2.66%), common sugars, proteins (11.29%), crude fiber (29%), energy, amino acid, carbohydrates (39%) and chlorophyll (
 Hassan and Umar, 2006; 
 Thakur et al., 2009; 
 Orhan et al., 2010; 
 Ibrahim et al., 2014; 
 Birla, 2016; 
 Abegunde et al., 2018).
